About this hotel

On a side street in the historic medina district, this polished riad in a striking Moorish building is a 13-minute walk from vendors and street performers at the bustling Jemaa el-Fnaa square. It’s 7 km from Marrakesh Menara Airport.

Check-in time: 2:00 PM
Check-out time: 11:00 AM

    Medina

    Hammam bath houses and covered spice and textile souks line the maze of cobblestoned lanes in the Medina, which occupies Marrakesh’s original fortified citadel. At night, Jemaa el-Fna square teems with snake charmers, folk dancers, and street food vendors serving all manner of food. Bahia Palace and Le Jardin Secret are 19th-century complexes open to the public, with ornate courtyards, mosaics, and gardens.

    About this hotel

    On a side street in the historic medina district, this polished riad in a striking Moorish building is a 13-minute walk from vendors and street performers at the bustling Jemaa el-Fnaa square. It’s 7 km from Marrakesh Menara Airport. …

    Colorful, warmly furnished rooms feature Wi-Fi access and en suite bathrooms; some have terraces or direct pool access. Suites add living rooms, plus kitchens or fireplaces.

    Breakfast is available. There’s a leafy, ornately tiled courtyard with an outdoor pool, plus a sundeck and multiple lounges.
